This paper is about training probabilistic neural networks using PAC-Bayes bounds, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of statistical learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions using backpropagation, which is a common optimization algorithm used in neural networks, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the method on various datasets, including image datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with risk minimization, which is a common problem in optimization and decision-making, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories.
